snippet.textDisplay:
It's cool he won, he absolutely deserves it. But man, what an awkward speech. The F-bombs and of course the vegetarian/vegan lifestyle praising, the Australia fires, etc. He did exactly what Ricky Gervais was kind of trying to say in his opening monologue not to do. He's a millionaire paid millions by not exactly the most virtuous people. He's in no position to lecture the general public, or even his peers.

Accept the award, thank whomever you want and fuck off. Damn right...I like that he's passionate about stuff, but I don't understand why some of these people feel the need to "raise awareness" and motivate others.
